{"word":"ἄψυχος","slug":"ἄψυχος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄψυχος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ψυχή'><el>ψυχή</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>lifeless, inanimate</i>, <b><a href='S:Simonides Lyricus'>Simon.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>ἄψ. βορά</el> <i>non-animal</i> food, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>spiritless, faint-hearted</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}